3.1 Justified Predictions Both expert systems and CBR systems may have an explanation component [14] in charge of justifying why the system has  provided a specific answer to the user.
The next section addresses this issue.
A justification built by a CBR method after determining that the solution of a particular problem P was Sk is a description that contains the relevant information from the problem P that the CBR method has considered to predict Sk as the solution of P. In particular , CBR methods work by retrieving similar cases to the problem at hand , and then reusing 